  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I had a quick look and search and found this: #1015\r\n\r\nIt is related. \r\n\r\n> So it won't still be able to perform a search from an external button without \"hack\" and getting the value from the input with JavaScript\r\n\r\nYes indeed. It's actually a regression from the #1015 issue. But then I'm wondering if we should have accepted that in the first place. Yes it's hacky when you want to be able to search using a button. But on the other hand it's inconsistent to update the url without searching. Since we update the URL based on the search state, and using the `search` event breaks the back button, I still think this sounds like a valid option.\r\n\r\nWDYT? @vvo @iam4x ",
